<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7126> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7126" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 49? The entry should probably read C. Sentius C. f. Sab. (4, see 9), unless there is a lacuna in Joseph. AJ 14.220. As he is listed last in the consilium of the consul in 49 (Joseph. AY 14.229), he was probably not yet a senator (cf. the position of the tr. mil. in the list in AJ 14.229), but was almost certainly a tr. mil. Münzer identifies him with Saturninus (see 9), the envoy in 40 (MRR 2.384; App. BC 5.52) and with Sentius Saturninus Vetulo (see 9), named in Val. Max. 7.3.9 (but cf. App. BC 4.45, where a similar story is told of a Pomponius), and with the father of C. Sentius C. f. C. n. Saturninus (9). Cos. 19 (see Groag, RE no. 9). In MRR 2.384, read (Sentius) Saturninus (Vetulo) (see 4 and 9). (TJC) '" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6955> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6955" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Member of the consilium of the Consul of 49 B. C. at Ephesus (Joseph. AJ 14.229)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6284> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6284" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Unofficial Envoys from Sextus Pompey to Antony in Greece in the summer of 40 (App. BC 5.52)." .
